			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>samuel446 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">high i always played with melee toons. I heard of kiting before but how do you do it with a necro.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">Lots of different ways to kite as a necro.  But the simple answer is to snare the mob, then apply damage while keeping yourself out of range.
<br />

<br />
Using the pet as a damage source requires that you prevent the mob from engaging the pet (if you want it to be considered a kite).  That can be accomplished either by use of the Fear spell line (aka Fear Kiting) or by generating enough aggro that the mob chases you while your pet beats on its back (aka aggro kiting).
<br />

<br />
Nothing else really to it.  Be carefull of pathing, especially when kiting social mobs.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
